ModelResponse(parts=[TextPart(content='{\n  "sparql_query": "\\nPREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>\\nPREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>\\nPREFIX 223: <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223#>\\nPREFIX ex: <http://data.ashrae.org/standard223/data/lbnl-example-2#>\\n\\nSELECT DISTINCT ?zone WHERE {\\n  # Zone instances\\n  ?zone a 223:Zone .\\n  \\n  # ---- 1) Directly associated property ----\\n  FILTER EXISTS { ?zone 223:hasProperty ?directProp . }\\n  \\n  # ---- 2) Indirectly connected via a RoomDomainSpace ----\\n  UNION {\\n    # Find a RoomDomainSpace reachable from the zone (any length of connections)\\n    ?zone (rdf:*|rdf:inverse*) ?room .\\n    ?room a ex:RoomDomainSpace .\\n    # From that RoomDomainSpace reach a property (any length of connections)\\n    ?room (rdf:*|rdf:inverse*) ?indirectProp .\\n    # The reached node must be a property of one of the known property classes\\n    ?indirectProp a ?propClass .\\n    FILTER(?propClass IN (\\n      223:QuantifiableObservableProperty,\\n      223:EnumeratedObservableProperty,\\n      223:QuantifiableActuatableProperty,\\n      223:EnumeratedActuatableProperty\\n    ))\\n  }\\n}\\n"\n}', part_kind='text')], model_name='hosted_vllm/hosted_vllm/gpt-oss-120b', timestamp=datetime.datetime(2026, 1, 22, 1, 34, 22, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), kind='response')
